# Global engineering defaults

## Communication

Apply the **caveman** skill at **ultra** intensity on every response unless the user says "stop caveman" or "normal mode". Code blocks, commits, and PR bodies stay normal.

## Projects (customize)

Add your repos here — stack, deploy target, naming quirks. Example:

```markdown
- **MyApp**: Next.js + Supabase. Deploy: Vercel.
- **MyApi**: Python/FastAPI. Deploy: Railway.
```

## Workflow

- Plan first for non-trivial tasks (3+ steps).
- Verify before marking done — run tests, check logs.
- Verify then commit — lint + build/test before committing.
- Prefer Read, Glob, Grep over broad exploration for known paths.

## Token efficiency (global stack)

| Layer | What | Where |
|-------|------|--------|
| **Output** | Caveman ultra — short replies | `caveman` skill |
| **Terminal** | `rtk <cmd>` on noisy CLI | `rtk` skill (requires [RTK](https://github.com) installed) |
| **Edits** | Read once before Write; Grep callers before signature changes | This rule |
| **Context** | Budget mode at 50%+; compact + checkpoint + archives | `session-memory` rule + hooks |
| **Safety** | Secret write block | `secret-guard` hook |
| **Frontend** | Impeccable (2D) or r3f-three (3D) when project has them | `frontend-design-pointer` rule + project install |

## Frontend (project-local)

Web app repos: `install-frontend.ps1` (Impeccable + ui-ux-pro-max). 3D/WebGL repos: `install-3d.ps1` (r3f-three). Not global. See `docs/FRONTEND.md` and `docs/3D.md`.

## Security invariants

- Scope every DB query to the session user.
- Return 404 (not 403) for unauthorised resource access.
- Rate limit auth + public endpoints before going live.
- Secrets in env vars — never in source code.
- Never read secret-bearing files — see `no-secret-file-reads` rule.
